I've lived in Chicago for 15 years and I go to Starbucks frequently and this is easily the most disgusting Starbucks I've ever been in. It used to be nicer in the 2000s. But for the past several years, its staff has been abrupt and rude (they ignore customers in line without a word), the inside has been consistently dirty (including dirty floors and tables and dried mucus stuck to the wall at face-level next to the rear banquette), and management has allowed people who are not customers to use the space (both inside and outside seating) as a personal living room--including homeless whom I've experienced begging inside and mentally challenged residents from the SRO around the corner. And it just gives this place a really unsettling, unsafe, out-of-control vibe--a vibe that includes the obvious fact that the staff who work here just don't care.  I live half a mile away but when I have a balance to use on my Starbucks card, I go out of my way to the Starbucks in Andersonville or Rogers Park--both at least half a mile farther away from my house--because of how awful the Bryn Mawr Starbucks always is now. If you aren't using a Starbucks card and you are looking for a coffee shop on Bryn Mawr, there are several other, much better options a block in either direction.

Honestly, this is the most disappointing Starbucks I've been to. I've tried it on two separate occasions because I believed the poor service the first time was a fluke - I was wrong. I went again today and ordered a simple iced green tea. I paid and went over to the pick up counter and waited...and waited...and waited. Orders from behind me were getting called out, and after 12 minutes I'd finally had it and asked the barista where my drink was. He said someone "must have grabbed it off the counter" but he would make me another one. Wrong, sir. I watched the entire time and not once was my green tea prepared. The place wasn't even busy, so I have no clue what the hold up was. He rolled his eyes and gave me attitude the whole time he was "re-making" my drink. Okay then. Would give 0 stars if I could. Go to literally any other Starbucks unless wasting 15 minutes on a mediocre drink is something you enjoy.

This place is hit or miss. The staff is GENERALLY polite and helpful, but there are a few characters who can be ornery.  There's one girl who seems to be the dysfunctional employee who messes up frequently and isn't remotely personable. The other day, I ordered a couple of things from her then stood there at the register for several minutes waiting for her to slowly go about getting my stuff (while those at the other register ordered, paid, then went to find a seat to wait). When I finally paid and got my things, she hadn't made me an ice water that I'd asked for, and when I asked the bearded guy at the espresso machine for one, he seemed annoyed then gave me the smallest plastic cup they had (a tall, I presume, though it seemed like an 8oz cup) and was unpleasant when I twice had to ask for a refill of said tiny over the next 15 minutes. Meanwhile, people who actually ordered and got their ice waters in the normal fashion are all drinking from grande or venti cups.  I come here frequently. 85% of the time, there's no complaints from me (aside from the people loudly chatting in Russian or Ethiopian or yelling into their phones, but that's no fault of this establishment or its workers), the rest of the time, it's generally trivial things they get wrong.  Still, a review I read here is not far off: on days spent working on my computer at this Starbucks, I hear many people who asked for iced or hot drinks but didn't get what they ordered, then have to stand there while they make it again or pour over ice. This group of employees/baristas need to listen to customers better or communicate with each other better!
